<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eustis</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-03"><hi rend="italic">May 3,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Waller’s stepson expelled from Madagascar is here, destitute. He has
                                Waller’s draft for $50 on the Secretary of Treasury for balance of
                                salary. Can it be cashed here? He knows all the facts. If you want
                                to see him, instruct me as to his passage. If not, how am I to
                                provide for him?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Eustis</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>